caption: ABSOLUTELY LOVE THIS PLACE. A hidden gem in Bed Stuy. The food has always been incredibly fresh and delicious. Their menu has so many options that anyone will find something they like. The owners are very friendly and always greet you like family. When I have friends or family visit I always bring them here. A+. Support this business !
Awesome and yummy food, I liked the character this place has, and the staff members were welcoming. Will definitely visit here next time.

Came here for a Covid small birthday dinner and not only is the food incredible, the service and ambience is fantastic! Highly recommend coming here for food and drinks. Such a fabulous experience which made it feel special again.
Had the fried chicken bento box and let me tell you...it tingled all my senses! I did pick up but the staff was very friendly and the indoor dining vibe looked nice!
Ordered delivery from here the other night.  Really good burger & sushi rolls!  Looking forward to dining in when we're allowed to.  Definitely recommend checking this spot out.
Best mexican food here!

Excellent food and customer service. The owners are super nice and friendly and genuinely care about their customer’s experience . Everything is exceptional. They even customize the food upon request. A must try!

My 2020 Japanese X-Perience  Since this restaurant was in her neighborhood. my Sista-Friend Crissi suggested this restaurant to us (5)..   When we arrived, we were excourted to the backyard space.  It was a perfect evening to sit outside in November, since it was 70+ degrees (11/7).  COVID-19 restrictions did not hinder our x-perience.  It felt like we were lifted out of Brooklyn and into a nice private | quiet space.  Our Waiter (the Owner) was totally AMAZING.  He made us feel like we were the ONLY guests dining at the restaurant, even thosugh there was other people dining outdoors. The food was total deliciousness.  Lots of variety and totally authentic Japanese food.  I would strongly recommend this restaurant.  The service | outdoor ambiance | delicious food choices | eclectic décor were AMAZING.

One of the best restaurants in a neighborhood with a lot of great restaurants. Trad Room is our favorite for weeknights, special occasions, a coffee to go, and everything in between. Plus, the owners are super kind and lovely.
Very good okay
This place has a really nice ambience, a limited, but delicious menu, and wonderful staff! Ideal for a dinner date.
Food is excellent. Proprietor is good natured.
I've been here a number of times an absolutely love the food, the coffee everything is delicious.  The owners are lovely and gracious, this is my top 5 place to eat in Bed Stuy.

Culinary masterpiece. Owner cares and serves you directly. Very attentive and respectful. If you are a foodie you will be very happy. Local gem. We ordered half of the menu and loved everything. Even desserts are quality and thoughtful.
This place is special.

Bland and tasteless. I was excited to try this place and thought with all of the great reviews it would be fabulous. Try adding some flavor! It was offensive. It’s possible their other food is better, but I got the short rib rice bowl, what a waste of money! Basically plain rice with a little soy sauce and some overcooked pieces of meat with no real flavor, couple onions and bell pepper thrown in there... I feel bad for the chef!

One of my favoriot restaurant located in Brooklyn. Their spicy chicken is the best chicken that I've ever had in NYC. I brought friends here too, they all love it too.  Very tasty food, organic, and unique.  With very nice staff and stylish environment.:)  Thanks for providing great food:)
Food is light and refreshing. Ambiance is nice very vintage trendy.
Was a super cute place! Their chai is amazing, and the food was excellent! I got their chicken curry.
Loved it! Had rich almond mocha, and great breakfast!  Enjoyed the serenity of the back patio space. The entire atmosphere was worth the visit!
Food was great! Ambient unique and vintage, lovely place.

I’ll give them more stars if Google allows me. Trad room is super cool yet cozy restaurant. Very jazzy yet comfy atmosphere. Food is fantastic. I went back several months after when they changed the menus seasonally. I like that fact that they have so many small plates to share so that I could get to try so many things at once. Perfect for all kinds of occasions, strongly recommended!!!!! Love to go back again.

My wife and I shared the Gem Salad, the Bakudan Tofu, the Chirashi, and the Rib Eye. For dessert we shared the Chocolate Fondante. One thing I loved about the vibe was all the plants and the old school analogue sound system that had the base grooves feeling warm and vivid. But to the food: the salad was crisp and refreshing, and the Bakudan tofu was also very good, with a mix of okra and house made Kimchi. The Kimchi has that nice effervescence that one only gets from lactic acid fermentation. Our waiter was very good and I’m glad he had recommended that we dice and mix the tofu prior to eating. This way all the flavors were present in each bite. The Chirashi was tasty and healthy, with a brown rice base and micro greens, the distribution and shape of the fish cuts reminded me of poké, more than traditional Chirashi, but tasty nontheless. the Ribeye was cooked perfectly medium rare, and the fries and mustard were on excellent side. The chocolate cake for dessert was perfect. Underneath the scoop of ice cream were crushed pistachios for some nice added texture and flavor. As of my visit they did not have their liquor license, but perhaps they are BYOB or are in the process of getting it. Great date spot. Fantastic value.

Fried chicken was amazing and grilled veggies too. Fantastic ambiance, great service and awesome background bluegrass music. Spot is also also perfect to bring your laptop or a book and enjoy the coffee

Today is my birthday so I decided to pick a local restaurant n Trad Room was my pick. Very cozy setting with soft music playing, a Japanese restaurant. So as soon as I saw the menu, I was disappointed. Not a large variety at all n no traditional Asian food. I really didn't no what to expect, but I assumed some type of dumplings but there was none. The waitress was very pleasant n you can see them prepare the food, so that was fine with me. I ordered the Asian Gem Salad, for me it was only ok n the Karrage Fried Chicken which was good. I will try it again once expand their menu.
Grest neighborhood coffee and food . Comfortable ,easy place to meet up, read, some private time for self. Offering daily specials and good food. We go for coffee and relaxation.
This is my go to restaurant.  The make a branzino that never fails.  I recently went to their brunch and it was delicious as well.  All food is made to perfection.

One of the best restaurants in Bed Stuy!!!!!!  You must get the nan ban chicken!!!  I am convinced that when people find out about this chicken, there will be a line out the door for this chicken!!  Their other food is excellent too, but that chicken is like crack, but healthier - you gotta try it!  It’s like japanese fried chicken, boneless thigh, deep fried, with this amazing tangy sauce that taste kind of like a Japanese version of tartar sauce, but much more complex than that.  Their steak is great too...  Everything is oishii (delicious)!
Food was mostly good. The duck ramen was super tasty and everyone else enjoyed their meals too. Portions are on the small side though and we didn't like the mushroom ajillo appetizer.
Great food and pricing, with excellent service!
Great food and neighborhood gem.
I love this place, the coffee and teas are absolutely magnificent!! The matcha is bonafide bonded! Their menus and Pastries are delicious
Not my taste.  But I can go here just to listen to the speakers. Won't find the warm and classic sound of them vintage horns anywhere else.
Good food but really bad service and slow. Took 30 min to get a breakfast and 20 min for a coffee.

I have been wandering around Brooklyn trying new restaurants and last night I stumbled upon Trad Room. The decor is super cool. I love that they don't serve alcohol. The server we had was in the weeds doing it all on his own but he was hustling and amazing. Now let's get to the food. Everything from the Chai latte, artichoke dip, mushrooms, ribeye, blackberry sorbet and lemon tart had SO MUCH FLAVOR. It was really excellent and a nice surprise.

American with a touch of Japanese influence. Staff are lovely. Went for breakfast. The menu we saw online didn't seem to be available. Saying that they still had good choice. We don't eat eggs so not as much choice for us. The French toast was nice. Our friends really enjoyed the mushroom toast. Nice atmosphere.
Very good 👍
Wonderful restaurant—really cool vibe and even better food! Get the artichoke dip!
Nice cosy place friendly staff. Very nice decorated. Food is okay.
beautiful atmosphere, great food and service.
Love this restaurant. Love the staff. Love the food. Love the decor. Love the owners. Love the owners' baby. Love the owner's motorcycle. There is nothing I don't like about this place.
Not a lot of salt in their food-- cool layout, but ultimately not flavorful-- and no alcohol
Cozy, rustic, antique vibes. Great food, drinks, and service. Fun spot. Nice outdoor patio as well in the back.
Great space with a really cool kitchen.
Awesome ambience, really kind owners, and eclectic food and good coffee!
Nice Brooklyn like restaurant. Steak is amazing. Do the Dan Dan Ramen at last.
Delicious Japanese tapas, decently priced
Ambiance is nice! The servers are seem to have a somber demeanor with the exception of the short guy with somewhat curly hair.
really good food and yummy oysters. dessert was really good!! super funky asian fusion decor. loved it!

The food is consistently excellent. I've been many times and always fully enjoy the culinary experiences available. I like to combine small plates in order for the table to sample multiple dishes.  The  Steak or the Branzino are great choices for an entree but I would encourage a visitor to try any of the dishes because they all please. It should be noted that they do not have a liquor license yet.
Wonderful staff and great service!
(Translated by Google) Good food excellent  (Original) Buena comida excelente
We had a nice quiet dinner and delicious dessert here. I love a BYOB option. They may want to do more with music but this place is a nice addition to the strip.
Friendly staff, and a nice atmosphere, but honestly the food seemed overpriced and a bit bland.
Great food, amazing service and the nicest atmosphere.
Great food and services. The AC could be more powerfull.
Great food and friendly staff, be advised that they don’t serve alcohol, witch is a pity when you get oysters for example

food was great

Hi this is Miriam from the Brooklyn Agency and today I came to your beautiful Trad Room and saw the amazing beautiful ambience and music and amazing calm place. Excellent service and great food. Highly recommended!!!!
Service was so so considering there were only 4 others tables dining. Moules are to be avoided . Burger seemed ok..chicken passable a bit rubbery.

An absolutely marvelous experience! Top quality service, delicious food and a very well thought through menu. The decorations and music fit the mood of the place perfectly. Shared all the mains and desserts with my family, so I can assure you they're absolutely splendid.

Some of the best food I've had in New York. We always get the shrimp ajillo, artichoke dip, and nanban chicken. The menu is so unique and will never disappoint. The service here is amazing and you can tell how much effort and love the owners put into building this into the community.

My favorite restaurant in the neighborhood!! Great food, great staff, and overall chill vibe! I try to come at least once a week... Food is always fresh and yummy! Must try the Nanban chicken, lamb gyozas, salmon bowl, fried chicken.. really can’t go wrong with anything! The matcha French toast for brunch is next level!!
The host is always extremely polite and the orders are always precised
Charming decor, quiet atmosphere. Very welcoming. Food was good, ordered Japanese Fried Chicken. I had house lemonade which was very tasty and great after a day in the NY heat.
Amazing place and excellent customer service.
Call me back
You go once for the experience. That's it.  And I would advise against it, if you were a friend.
Great food, comfortable relaxed vibe. Wonderful experience overall.
Great menu, super friendly staff  Also the Japanese fried chicken is bananas
Lovely experience. The Salmon and brown Rice was lovely and the service was wonderful.
Service was not great but the oysters was delicious

Friendly !

They have like 30 two tops here, and he insisted on seating us directly next to the only group in the restaurant due to “everything being plotted out for the night”. I’ve eaten the food before, it’s really great. we got up and left and I won’t go back ever again. So unnecessary my guy
Really delicious food & very good service! Great environment!!!
Just okay, but a decently priced stop for a weeknight.

Nice, big space with chilled music and pleasant staff.  We stopped in for an iced latte and a matcha latte and got a table really easily.  They have free WiFi, take card and lots of space for groups to sit.

Love the environment. Very fun menu. I got the pork katsu. It w a fine. Much prettier than how it tastes.
Solid spot, tucked away on Malcolm X so it’s never too busy. Great service. No liquor license so keep that in mind. The pork katsu rice had some uncooked rice grains that were a little un pleasant.

First off, it's a very quiet an comfy space. Wheelchair friendly, they serve coffees, tea's, espresso an juices. The menu is really nice, it's a Japanese inspired menu. If your looking for regular menu items this is not the place lol, the service was real nice. The waiter was really cool an laid back, the staff also real cool. I will definitely be back to try other options on their menu.
Excellent food and service!
The food was absolutely delicious; one of the best meals I've had in my time living in Bed-Stuy. And the ambiance was warm and inviting, I felt like I was in a Murakami novel!

Excellent place to have a really good dinner. Oysters are really really good and fresh.
Food is really delicious and quite varied — it’s an eclectic menu.

Good food and portions, serving a really good cup of coffee.  Nice vibe, good music.  Only detractor, is they don't yet have a liquor license. But if you're really in need of a drink, there's a liquor store 50 feet away and a great little bar a block up that's got you covered.  Great for breakfast, and will be a great Dinner/Oyster spot once the liquor license comes through.  Food's still really good, looking forward to Oysters and Wine/drinks once they get their license.
Very friendly staff, with a cute baby in a sling and some delicious happy hour oysters!  Will come again!
Went here for a book club get together. Really nice vibe! My only complaint is the jazz music was a tad bit too loud, but I will be coming back! Very cozy!
Food is f* good! Amazing experience, great music and awesome atmosphere!
Amazing espresso! It's surprisingly hard to find a not burnt espresso in the NYC and Brooklyn area. But I did find a great one here. The seared salmon was amazing and tasted fresh and sushi like.

If you feel like all menus look the same and all food taste the same -satisfactory but not... great -, and you want your taste buds to feel excited again, this is the place for you. This adorable place is a hidden gem in bedstuy: amazing oyster happy hour, great TASTY vegetarian options and very reasonable prices. Go, run, and thank me (and them) later!!!!

Absolutely wonderful!!  hands down best ambience of any cafe that I know in the area -- quiet, peaceful, beautiful.  Food is top notch, with an excellent selection of teas and great coffee.  highly recommend coming here to work and have a snack.
Great food and friendly warm vibe. I would be a regular if I lived a bit closer.
Amazing atmosphere and creative food. Just what this neighborhood was needing. Fresh oysters daily. Cozy sound of vintage audio. All very tasteful.

Went last night for the first time! The place is great. Atmosphere is spot on and the food is delicious. They are currently in the process of getting their liquor license and when they do it will no doubt be a busy buzzing place. I plan on going often.

The one issue is the server, he was rude, seemed to have a problem with people from this neighborhood and had a bad attitude about everything. Just drop the server boy and get someone from this neighborhood who wants to work hard for an establishment with this level of food and you got yourself a winning combination.
